// EXPECT: 129
// Campaign Latent Type-Inference (Lát 1): a bare `let x = <integer literal>`
// must stamp x's local with MirType::Integer so `match x` reaches the
// value-keyed Integer dispatch (ADR-0064) instead of falling through to the
// enum-path and refusing. Before the literal-arm fix, the literal local was
// MirType::Unknown → lowerer error "unsupported match pattern (expected enum
// variant): Literal(Integer{value:1})". This is the exact repro fixture 215
// flagged as out-of-scope ("a bare `let x = 2` infers MirType::Unknown").
//
// Each branch uses a literal-init let (NOT a param/identifier-init, which would
// already be typed and make this vacuous). pick1=10 (case), pick2=20 (case),
// pick9=99 (wildcard). 10 + 20 + 99 = 129 — a broken case mapping, lost
// wildcard, or un-typed scrutinee changes the total or refuses to lower.
function pick1() -> Integer = { let x = 1; match x { 1 => 10, 2 => 20, _ => 99 } }
function pick2() -> Integer = { let x = 2; match x { 1 => 10, 2 => 20, _ => 99 } }
function pick9() -> Integer = { let x = 9; match x { 1 => 10, 2 => 20, _ => 99 } }

function main() -> Integer = pick1() + pick2() + pick9()
